Similarly to the <a href="../cgsbog">BOG</a> build, PCBs are supported on an aluminium frame held in place place by small brackets and stand-offs.

<h2>Modifications</h2>

When I designed the front panels, I made a mistake and thought that the Rate input on the Smooth/Stepped and Random Source modules was an attenuverter, but it turns out that this isn't the case. To rectify this (and add a bit of functionality) I designed a PCB to keep a dedicated attenuverter circuit based on the <a href="https://kassu2000.blogspot.com/2018/04/precision-attenuverter-mixer.html">Kassutronics Precision Attenuverter</a> circuit. This allows for a finer control around the centre position of the potentiometer.

